This paper is about dialogue generation using adversarial imitation learning and adversarial inverse reinforcement learning. The main focus is on improving the reward signal for the generator, which is a key component in adversarial dialogue generation models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as imitation learning and inverse reinforcement learning, which are covered by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance evaluation of the proposed model, which falls under cs.SD (Sound) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
